snippet.title: The must-watch moments of the CNN Presidential Debate
snippet.description:
Catch up on the biggest moments of CNN’s Presidential Debate between President Joe Biden and former President Donald Trump. 

Watch the full replay of the CNN Presidential Debate here: https://www.youtube.com/live/-v-8wJkmwBY

Want to stay up to date on the day’s top stories? Sign up for CNN’s 5 Things newsletter, and we’ll give you the 5 biggest stories you need to know, videos people are watching, and more!

replies.comment_text: There are plenty of better options but the sad part is they don't stand a chance. America has a two party system. Most people are divided between these two parties. There are some third party options but the problem is that voting third party takes a vote away from the two main parties when there is a near 50 50 split. Say you prefer Biden over Trump but you vote third party. That is less votes for your second choice person who stands a better chance at winning than the 3rd party person you voted for. They both get less votes. That 50 50 split becomes 50/25/25 (or 50/46/4 and etc. Regardless there is no roughly even split) if the other party stays strong and doesn't vote third party, they will get more votes so now the person who is your last choice wins the election.
